%S A351516 0,0,6,6,8,12,20,24,30,36,48
%N A351516 a(n) is the maximum number of 3-letter words that can be contained in an n X n crossword puzzle.
%C A351516 The n X n crossword puzzle grid must contain the maximum number of 3-letter words (and no words of other lengths), and all words must be interconnected (i.e., no word or set of connected words can be completely separated from the other words).
%C A351516 The magazine Humor y Juegos Number 13 says that Mariano Pablo Amieva and Solomon Golomb found a general answer to this problem.
%D A351516 Jaime Poniachik, Las matemáticas del crucigrama, Revista Humor y Juegos, Número 9, ~ 1981.
%H A351516 Rodolfo Kurchan, <a href="https://www.puzzlefun.online/puzzle-fun-35">Problem 781</a>, Puzzle Fun 35, December 2021.
